The Tony Elumelu Foundation has announced a partnership with the United Nations Development programme to empower 100,000 entrepreneurs, over a ten year period. The announcement was made public on the official Instagram page of the Tony Elumelu Foundation saying; “We are pleased to announce the partnership between the Tony Elumelu Foundation and @UNDP to empower 100,000 additional entrepreneurs in 7 Sahel African countries over a 10-year period.
With this partnership, the Tony Elumelu Foundation gives hope to the thousands of African entrepreneurs who have not been selected for its TEF Entrepreneurship Programme. With more partners on the way, we hope to do much more – we are unleashing the potential of the African continent! Starting this July, applications open for African entrepreneurs residing in the following countries: Nigeria (Northern), Niger, Chad, Cameroun, Mauritania, Mali and Burkina Faso”. Follow us on Instagram and Twitter for updates. The post Tony Elumelu Foundation Partners With UN Development Programme To Empower 100,000 Entrepreneurs appeared first on Olori Supergal. Source: Olori Super Gal The Tony Elumelu Foundation (TEF) last week turned seven and the founder called for a reflection of how his foundation “has grown and how our ambitions have risen to the challenges, are moving towards achieving scale and continent-wide impact.” Seven years ago, Tony Elumelu, Chairman of United Bank for Africa… November 6, 2017 In "News" Photo: Tony Elumelu/Twitter The founder of Tony Elumelu Foundation (TEF), Heirs Holding and Chairman of United Bank for Africa (UBA), Tony Elumelu, will host the largest gathering of African entrepreneurs in the world in Lagos, the former capital city of Nigeria, at the TEF Entrepreneurship Forum, tomorrow. The forum is a two-day… October 13, 2017 In "News" <ul><li>Tony Elumelu Foundation (TEF) shortlists 3,050 successful applicants for the 2019 cohort of the Foundationâ€™s flagship Entrepreneurship Programme.</li><li>The 3,050 successful applicants for the 2019 TEF cohort represents 58%% male, 42%% female.</li><li>Some of the parameters used in selecting applicants include feasibility, market opportunity, scalability, leadership skill and viability of the idea.</li><li>The… March 22, 2019 In "News"